==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|capitalisme|lang=fr||the condition of one who is rich}}. First used in English by novelist [[w:William Thackeray|William Thackeray]] in 1854.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{context|politics|uncountable|lang=en}} a socio-economic system based on private property rights, including the private ownership of resources or [[capital]], with economic decisions made largely through the operation of a market [[unregulated]] by the [[state]].
# {{context|economics|uncountable|lang=en}} a socio-economic system based on the abstraction of resources into the form of privately owned [[capital]], with economic decisions made largely through the operation of a market [[unregulated]] by the [[state]].
# {{context|countable|lang=en}} a specific variation or implementation of either such socio-economic system.

